               <history>
                  <origin notBefore="1300" notAfter="1399" cert="high" evidence="conjecture">Written
                     in <origPlace>Noway</origPlace> in <origDate notBefore="1300" notAfter="1399"
                        >s. XIV<hi>1</hi>, c. 1300 and s. XIV ex</origDate>. <list>
                        <item>Fols 1ra-60vb:21 can de dated to the first half of the fourteenth
                           century (e.g. <bibl><ref target="NgL4">Storm 1885</ref><biblScope
                                 unit="page">564</biblScope></bibl> and <bibl><ref target="KKKat"
                                 >Kålund's catalogue</ref></bibl>) </item>
                        <item>Fols 60vb:22-61rb can be dated to c. 1350 (<bibl><ref target="NgL4"
                                 >Storm 1885</ref><biblScope unit="page"
                           >565</biblScope></bibl>)</item>
                        <item>Fols 61va-vb can be dated to the end of the fourteenth century
                                 (<bibl><ref target="NgL4">ibid.</ref></bibl>).</item>
                     </list> Kålund (<bibl><ref target="KKKat">Katalog</ref></bibl>) dated fols
                     60vb-61vb to the second half of the fourteenth century.</origin>
                  <provenance>From the AM-slips it appears that <name type="person" key="PedSyv001"
                        >Peder Syv</name> of <name type="place">Hellested</name>, <country key="DK"
                        >Denmark</country> gave the manuscript to <name type="person"
                        key="FreRos001">Frederik Rostgård</name>. <q>
                        <name type="person">IONAS MAGNI.</name>
                        <lb/> ANNO <date when="1598">1598</date>
                     </q> was written on the previous binding and on the pastedown the name <q>
                        <name type="person" key="JacAnd001">Jacob Anderſsön</name>
                     </q> was added. </provenance>
                  <acquisition>
                     <name type="person" key="FreRos001">Rostgård</name> presented <name
                        type="person" key="ArnMag001">Árni Magnússon</name> with the manuscript. It
                     was then bound together with a translation into Danish (<ref type="ms"
                        target="#AM04-0075-en">AM 75 4to</ref>). Árni separated the translation from
                     the source text and had AM 71 4to re-bound.</acquisition>
               </history>
